description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Multiple Sclerosis nurse seeking to develop your career in a supportive varied environment? Do you enjoy supporting patients with MS? We are looking for someone to help us build and create an MS service which is fit for the future, working in collaboration with our hospitals, community and GP partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post involves working autonomously within the hospital and community, being part of a small and friendly MS team and joining a large multidisciplinary team within the hospital. You will be providing specialist nursing support, education, healthcare liaison, and a high quality of care to all persons affected by MS in specialist clinics at Guys and St Thomas Hospitals and across our integrated care services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be excellent opportunities to teach and to help further your own professional development through internal and external courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has MS experience; however we are willing to consider applicants with less experience as part of a training role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are enthusiastic, passionate about what you do, strive to deliver high quality patient care, and want to make a difference to the care we provide for patients suffering with Multiple Sclerosis, then we would like to hear from you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits to the department are strongly encouraged. Please contact gail.simpson@gstt.nhs.uk or michelle.knapper@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews Planned for week beginning 16th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
